<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 10pt">10. On Begun see Begun's Chapter 1 (1949) ; Beverley
Gooch's Chapter 6 of <i>Magnetic Recording: the First 100
Years </i>(1999); letter from Ralph J. Oace to Bert S. Groves,
1964 Jan. 31. </span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 10pt">11. On motion picture sound see Belton (1992). </span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 10pt">12. On the magnetic drum see Schoenherr "The Magnetic
Drum" (2003). </span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 10pt">13. On UNIVAC see Gray (2001); on SAGE see Spicer
(2000) and Schoenherr "The SAGE Air Defense" (2000). </span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 10pt">14. On RAMAC see Johnson (1989); Schoenherr "The
Floppy Disk" (2003). </span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 10pt">15. On tape recorders see Angus (1984); Grundig history
(2002); Nagra history (2002); Sony history (2002); Studer
history (2002). </span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 10pt">16. On the VTR see Nmungwun's Chapter 6 (1989);
Ginsburg (1957). </span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 10pt">17. On helical scan, see Nmungwun's Chapter 7 (1989);
Schoenherr "Television Instant Replay" (2002). </span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 10pt">18. On the cassette see Morton's Chapter 8 "The Eight
Track Tape Cartridge" in his "History of Magnetic
Recording" (1995). </span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 10pt">19. On the Walkman see David Frith (1999). </span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 10pt">20. On Dee Hock and the credit card, see Mandell (1990). </span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 10pt">21. On the floppy disk see Schoenherr "The Floppy Disk"
(2003) . </span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 10pt">22. On Shugart see Schoenherr "The Floppy Disk" (2003). </span></span></p>
<p style="text-align: justify; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif"><span style="font-size: 10pt">23. On the digital revolution, see Schoenherr "The Digital
Revolution" (2001). </span></span></p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0.0625in; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom: 0.0625in; text-indent: 0.0983333in; margin-bottom: 0.0625in">&#160;</p>
